cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the automated detection of lesion borders in dermoscopy images. It may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves the evaluation of different methods for border detection. Additionally, it could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) as dermoscopy images are a type of medical multimedia. Machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the use of objective measures for evaluating the performance of different border detection methods.
